Parameter or Variable: TEMPERATURE - WATER - CONTINUOUS MEASUREMENT [WATER TEMPERATURE] (measured); 
Units: degrees Celsius; 
Observation Category: in situ; 
Sampling Instrument: SBE 19plus V2 SeaCAT Profiler CTD; 
Sampling and Analyzing Method: Conductivity, temperature, and depth sensor (CTD) data was collected by allowing the sensors to stabilize underwater, bringing the instrument to the surface, and then dropping it slowly. Values reported are the mean of all recorded values ±0.5m of the sample depth from the downcast of the instrument.; 
Data Quality Method: Expert review.

